@page "/learn/rebalancing"
@layout MacroSutra.Web.Components.Layout.LandingLayout

<PageTitle>MacroSutra - Portfolio Rebalancing Guide</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-section">
    <div class="landing-container">
        <h1>Portfolio Rebalancing</h1>
        <p>Define target allocations for your portfolio, detect drift from those targets, and execute rebalancing trades to bring your portfolio back in line.</p>

        <h2 id="targets" class="mt-4">Setting Up Rebalance Targets</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Portfolio &rarr; Rebalance</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>New Target</strong>.</li>
            <li>Give it a name (e.g., "60/40 Portfolio"), select a brokerage account, and set a <strong>drift threshold</strong> (default: 5%).</li>
            <li>Add allocation targets &mdash; each one specifies a symbol and a target percentage. Allocations should sum to 100%.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Create</strong>.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="drift" class="mt-4">Understanding Drift</h2>
        <p>Drift is the difference between a symbol's actual portfolio weight and its target weight. For example:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If VTI should be 60% of your portfolio but has grown to 72%, the drift is <strong>+12%</strong>.</li>
            <li>If BND should be 40% but has shrunk to 28%, the drift is <strong>-12%</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>MacroSutra flags the portfolio as needing rebalancing when any symbol's drift exceeds the configured threshold.</p>

        <h2 id="analysis" class="mt-4">Running an Analysis</h2>
        <p>Click <strong>Analyze</strong> on a rebalance target to see:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Total Portfolio Value</strong> &mdash; Sum of all position market values.</li>
            <li><strong>Per-Symbol Drift</strong> &mdash; Actual vs. target percentage and the dollar amount to trade to reach the target.</li>
            <li><strong>Needs Rebalancing</strong> &mdash; Whether any drift exceeds your threshold.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="executing" class="mt-4">Executing a Rebalance</h2>
        <p>Click <strong>Execute Rebalance</strong> to place market orders that bring each symbol back to its target weight:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Overweight positions are sold.</li>
            <li>Underweight positions are bought.</li>
            <li>Only symbols with drift above the threshold are traded.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each trade is recorded on the Trades page with a note indicating it was a rebalance trade.</p>

        <h2 id="api" class="mt-4">SDK &amp; API</h2>
<pre><code>// Analyze drift
var analysis = await client.Portfolio.AnalyzeRebalanceAsync(targetId);

// Execute rebalance orders
var trades = await client.Portfolio.ExecuteRebalanceAsync(targetId);</code></pre>

        <p class="mt-4"><a href="/learn">&larr; Back to Learn</a></p>
    </div>
</section>
